"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H13954902\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is aplastic anemia?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Aplastic anemia is a condition that happens when a person has too few blood cells. There are 3 different types of blood cells:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Red blood cells &ndash; These cells carry oxygen to your body.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        White blood cells &ndash; These cells fight infections.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Platelets &ndash; Platelets are actually pieces of cells, not whole cells. They help clots forms so that you stop bleeding after you are injured.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Blood cells are made in the middle of your bones, in a part called the bone marrow. Aplastic anemia happens when your body stops making enough of all 3 types of cells at the same time.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H13954917\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What causes aplastic anemia?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Aplastic anemia is caused by damage to your bone marrow. Some people are born with damaged bone marrow. In older children or adults, many things can damage bone marrow, including:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Certain medicines used to treat arthritis and epilepsy",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Certain chemicals used in industry and farming",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Infections from viruses",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Problems with your body&rsquo;s infection fighting system",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      But for many people, doctors don&rsquo;t know the cause of aplastic anemia.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H13954932\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of aplastic anemia?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Symptoms include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Feeling very tired",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A fast heartbeat",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Trouble breathing when you move around",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Getting infections often",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Having more bleeding than normal from the skin, nose, or gums",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Women with aplastic anemia might bleed more than normal during their menstrual periods.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H13954947\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for aplastic anemia?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Tests include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Blood tests, including a &ldquo;complete blood count&rdquo; or &ldquo;CBC&rdquo;",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Bone marrow biopsy &ndash; For this test, a doctor will take a very small sample of the bone marrow. Then another doctor will look at the cells under a microscope.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H13954962\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is aplastic anemia treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;The treatment depends on the cause of your aplastic anemia. Treatment can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Stopping medicines that caused the problem",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Staying away from toxic chemicals",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Medicines &ndash; These can include:",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"hyphen-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Antibiotics and anti-viral medicines",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Medicines that reduce the activity of your body&rsquo;s infection-fighting system (called &ldquo;immunosuppressive&rdquo; medicines)",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Blood transfusion &ndash; During a blood transfusion, you will get blood that has been donated by someone else. The donated blood goes into your vein through a small tube called an &ldquo;IV.&rdquo;",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Bone marrow transplant (also called a &ldquo;stem cell transplant&rdquo;) &ndash; This procedure replaces abnormal or missing cells in the bone marrow with healthy cells from a donor. These cells are given through an &ldquo;IV.&rdquo;",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
